            <abstract id="ref20" label="Abstract">The collection contains documents pertaining to the establishment of the Connecticut Transportation Institute at the University of Connecticut.</abstract>
        </did>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents</head>
            <p>The collection consists of copies of the papers read at the conference inaugurating the Connecticut Transportation Institute in 1974.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>History</head>
            <p>"The 1974 
                <geogname>Connecticut</geogname> Legislature, through Public Act 370, directed the 
                <corpname>University of Connecticut</corpname>, with the cooperation of the Department of Transportation, to plan and develop a program for the establishment of a 
                <corpname>Connecticut Transportation Institute</corpname>, to be operative for the fall semester of 1975. "</p>
            <p>"In response to the legislative mandate, a nine member committee was appointed by Vice President 
                <persname>Kenneth G. Wilson</persname> from among the engineering, science, business and humanities faculties; Dr. 
                <persname>Peter McFadden</persname>, Dean of the School of Engineering, was named chairman. Upon recommendation of the Committee, President 
                <persname>Glenn Ferguson</persname> appointed Dr. 
                <persname>Jack E. Stephens</persname> of the Department of Civil Engineering as Acting Director. Under this arrangement, the Transportation Institute Advisory Committee acted both as a policymaking board and a working committee. The committee and Dr. Stephens, with a modest amount of consultive assistance, and with the cooperation and assistance of the 
                <corpname>Connecticut Department of Transportation</corpname>, has undertaken to prepare a realistic plan for a transportation institute that will effectively eliminate an important deficiency in our capabilities in regard to transportation problem-solving."</p>
            <p>[from "A Program for the Development of the Connecticut Transportation Institute" located in the records.]</p>
            <p>Additional information about the Institute, its programs, faculty and goals is available on the CTI 
                <extref ns2:actuate="onRequest" ns2:show="new" ns2:href="http://www.cti.uconn.edu/">website</extref>.</p>
        </bioghist>
